properties.Title: Freezing Rain Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Freezing rain is expected. A period of freezing rain is expected this morning. In areas of higher terrain, freezing rain may continue into the early afternoon. Untreated surfaces such as roads, particularly bridges and overpasses, and walkways may also become icy. ### Poor weather conditions may contribute to transportation delays. properties.Title: Snow Squall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Variable conditions in snow squalls. A brisk west to southwesterly flow will continue to generate flurries and snow squalls today. The freshly fallen snow will combine the gusty windy and cold temperatures to produce blizzard-like conditions at times, with poor visibilities in blowing snow. The flurries and squalls are expected to gradually weaken during the day today, with clearing skies to follow tonight. Accumulations will vary considerably depending on the locations of the more intense squalls, with additional amounts of up to 5 cm. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Special Air Quality Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: DUST ADVISORY ISSUED FOR GOLDEN April 4, 2019 - Vernon. The Ministry of Environment and Climate Change Strategy, in collaboration with the Interior Health Authority, has issued a Dust Advisory for Golden due to high concentrations of coarse particulates, which are expected to persist until there is a change in current weather conditions. Persons with chronic underlying medical conditions should postpone strenuous exercise until the advisory is lifted. Staying indoors and in air-conditioned spaces helps to reduce particulate exposure. Exposure is particularly a concern for infants, the elderly and those who have diabetes, and lung or heart disease. ### For more information on current air quality, visit www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/environment/air-land-water/air. Visit www.airhealth.ca for information on how to reduce your health risk and your personal contribution to pollution levels, as well as for current and forecast AQHI values. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.

properties.Title: Snow Squall Watch In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Variable conditions can be expected today, with potential for persistent snow squalls. Flurries and local snow squalls will continue to combine with strong winds and cold temperatures to create areas of poor visibility in blowing snow. The potential exists for some of the squalls to become more persistent, resulting in localized near-blizzard conditions. An improving trend is expected for this afternoon. ### Travel may be hazardous due to sudden changes in the weather. Snow squall watches are issued when conditions are favourable for the formation of bands of snow that could produce intense accumulating snow or near zero visibilities. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.
